COPPER MOUNTAIN SOLAR 5, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Copper Mountain Solar 5, LLC ("Copper Mountain") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Copper Mountain generating facility ("Copper Mountain Facility").
The Copper Mountain Facility is a solar generating facility located in Clark County, Nevada. The Copper Mountain Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Nevada Power Company d/b/a NV Energy.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Copper Mountain's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Copper Mountain Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission through March 10, 2022.
Copper Mountain's fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Reactive Service Revenue Requirement for the period January 20, 2022 through March 10, 2022 is: $150,000.00.
